---
description: Next.js frontend rules (Admin Portal + Agent Portal)
globs: frontend/**, src/**, app/**, components/**, hooks/**, lib/**
---

Frontend stack:
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS 3.4
- TanStack React Query for server state
- Zustand for client state (auth, call, notifications)
- Axios for API calls (with JWT interceptor and auto-refresh)
- Socket.IO Client for real-time events
- @twilio/voice-sdk for browser-based calling
- Recharts for analytics charts
- ReactFlow for visual lead flow designer
- Lucide React for icons
- React Hook Form + Zod for form validation

Frontend rules:
- Prefer TypeScript for all frontend logic.
- Keep components small, reusable, and focused.
- Keep presentation separate from business/data-fetching logic.
- Use hooks for data fetching (TanStack Query) and Zustand stores for global state.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly.
- Preserve design consistency and naming consistency.
- Support real-time updates (Socket.IO) for live transcript, sentiment, AI guidance, and red flag alerts.
- **Two portals in one app:** Admin (`/(dashboard)/admin/*`) and Agent (`/(dashboard)/agent/*`); use role-based routing and layout; shared design system and API client.

Existing frontend structure (do not reorganize):
- frontend/src/app/(auth)/          (login, register, forgot-password)
- frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/     (admin and agent portal routes)
- frontend/src/components/ui/       (Button, Input, Modal, Table, Card, Badge, Toast, etc.)
- frontend/src/hooks/
- frontend/src/lib/                 (api.ts, socket.ts, twilio.ts, utils.ts, constants.ts)
- frontend/src/stores/              (auth-store, call-store, notification-store)
- frontend/src/types/               (models, api, call, lead, prediction)
- frontend/src/styles/

UI/UX rules:
- Use accessible markup and semantic HTML.
- Prefer reusable design system components from components/ui/.
- Avoid oversized page components.
- Avoid embedding complex API logic directly inside visual components.

State/data rules:
- Keep API client centralized in lib/api.ts.
- Use TanStack Query for server data; Zustand for auth/call/notification state.
- Handle auth state carefully (JWT refresh, redirect on 401).
- Validate critical inputs on both client and server.

Do not:
- Mix many responsibilities into one component.
- Hardcode API URLs in components; use environment variables via lib/constants.ts.
- Duplicate UI patterns that should be shared from components/ui/.
- Import server-only code in client components.
